<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no" name="viewport"><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="_TheLordTitlesAndRL.css" /></head><body>

<div class="c290_3"> 
<div id="v290.3.1"><span class="H113 s">For, behold, the Lord</span><span class="H3068 s">, the LORD</span><span class="H6635 s"> of hosts</span><span class="H5493 s">, doth take away</span><span class="H3389 s"> from Jerusalem</span><span class="H3063 s"> and from Judah</span><span class="H4937 s"> the stay</span><span class="H4938 s"> and the staff</span><span class="H4937 s">, the whole stay</span><span class="H3899 s"> of bread</span><span class="H3605 s">, and the whole</span><span class="H4937 s"> stay</span><span class="H4325 s"> of water</span>,</div> 
<div id="v290.3.2"><span class="H1368 s">The mighty man</span><span class="H376 s">, and the man</span><span class="H4421 s"> of war</span><span class="H8199 s">, the judge</span><span class="H5030 s">, and the prophet</span><span class="H7080 s">, and the prudent</span><span class="H2205 s">, and the ancient</span>,</div> 
<div id="v290.3.3"><span class="H8269 s">The captain</span><span class="H2572 s"> of fifty</span><span class="H5375 s">, and the honourable</span><span class="H6440 s"> man</span><span class="H3289 s">, and the counsellor</span><span class="H2450 s">, and the cunning</span><span class="H2791 s"> artificer</span><span class="H995 s">, and the eloquent</span><span class="H3908 s"> orator</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the honourable…: Heb. a man eminent in countenance) (eloquent…: or, skilful of speech)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.3.4"><span class="H5414 s">And I will give</span><span class="H5288 s"> children</span><span class="H8269 s"> <i>to be</i> their princes</span><span class="H8586 s">, and babes</span><span class="H4910 s"> shall rule</span> over them.</div> 
<div id="v290.3.5"><span class="H5971 s">And the people</span><span class="H5065 s"> shall be oppressed</span><span class="H376 s">, every one</span><span class="H376 s"> by another</span><span class="H376 s">, and every one</span><span class="H7453 s"> by his neighbour</span><span class="H5288 s">: the child</span><span class="H7292 s"> shall behave himself proudly</span><span class="H2205 s"> against the ancient</span><span class="H7034 s">, and the base</span><span class="H3513 s"> against the honourable</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.3.6"><span class="H376 s">When a man</span><span class="H8610 s"> shall take hold</span><span class="H251 s"> of his brother</span><span class="H1004 s"> of the house</span><span class="H1 s"> of his father</span><span class="H8071 s">, <i>saying</i>, Thou hast clothing</span><span class="H7101 s">, be thou our ruler</span><span class="H4384 s">, and <i>let</i> this ruin</span><span class="H3027 s"> <i>be</i> under thy hand</span>:</div> 
<div id="v290.3.7"><span class="H3117 s">In that day</span><span class="H5375 s"> shall he swear</span><span class="H559 s">, saying</span><span class="H2280 s">, I will not be an healer</span><span class="H1004 s">; for in my house</span><span class="H3899 s"> <i>is</i> neither bread</span><span class="H8071 s"> nor clothing</span><span class="H7760 s">: make</span><span class="H7101 s"> me not a ruler</span><span class="H5971 s"> of the people</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (swear: Heb. lift up the hand) (healer: Heb. binder up)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.3.8"><span class="H3389 s">For Jerusalem</span><span class="H3782 s"> is ruined</span><span class="H3063 s">, and Judah</span><span class="H5307 s"> is fallen</span><span class="H3956 s">: because their tongue</span><span class="H4611 s"> and their doings</span><span class="H3068 s"> <i>are</i> against the LORD</span><span class="H4784 s">, to provoke</span><span class="H5869 s"> the eyes</span><span class="H3519 s"> of his glory</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.3.9"><span class="H1971 s">The shew</span><span class="H6440 s"> of their countenance</span><span class="H6030 s"> doth witness against them</span><span class="H5046 s">; and they declare</span><span class="H2403 s"> their sin</span><span class="H5467 s"> as Sodom</span><span class="H3582 s">, they hide</span><span class="H188 s"> <i>it</i> not. Woe</span><span class="H5315 s"> unto their soul</span><span class="H1580 s">! for they have rewarded</span><span class="H7451 s"> evil</span> unto themselves.</div> 
<div id="v290.3.10"><span class="H559 s">Say</span><span class="H6662 s"> ye to the righteous</span><span class="H2896 s">, that <i>it shall be</i> well</span><span class="H398 s"> <i>with him</i>: for they shall eat</span><span class="H6529 s"> the fruit</span><span class="H4611 s"> of their doings</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.3.11"><span class="H188 s">Woe</span><span class="H7563 s"> unto the wicked</span><span class="H7451 s">! <i>it shall be</i> ill</span><span class="H1576 s"> <i>with him</i>: for the reward</span><span class="H3027 s"> of his hands</span><span class="H6213 s"> shall be given</span> him. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (given…: Heb. done to him)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.3.12"><span class="H5971 s"><i>As for</i> my people</span><span class="H5953 s">, children</span><span class="H5065 s"> <i>are</i> their oppressors</span><span class="H802 s">, and women</span><span class="H4910 s"> rule</span><span class="H5971 s"> over them. O my people</span><span class="H833 s">, they which lead</span><span class="H8582 s"> thee cause <i>thee</i> to err</span><span class="H1104 s">, and destroy</span><span class="H1870 s"> the way</span><span class="H734 s"> of thy paths</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (lead…: or, call thee blessed) (destroy: Heb. swallow up)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.3.13"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H5324 s"> standeth up</span><span class="H7378 s"> to plead</span><span class="H5975 s">, and standeth</span><span class="H1777 s"> to judge</span><span class="H5971 s"> the people</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.3.14"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H935 s"> will enter</span><span class="H4941 s"> into judgment</span><span class="H2205 s"> with the ancients</span><span class="H5971 s"> of his people</span><span class="H8269 s">, and the princes</span><span class="H1197 s"> thereof: for ye have eaten up</span><span class="H3754 s"> the vineyard</span><span class="H1500 s">; the spoil</span><span class="H6041 s"> of the poor</span><span class="H1004 s"> <i>is</i> in your houses</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (eaten: or, burnt)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.3.15"><span class="H1792 s">What mean ye <i>that</i> ye beat</span><span class="H5971 s"> my people</span><span class="H1792 s"> to pieces</span><span class="H2912 s">, and grind</span><span class="H6440 s"> the faces</span><span class="H6041 s"> of the poor</span><span class="H5002 s">? saith</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span><span class="H6635 s"> of hosts</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.3.16"><span class="H3068 s">Moreover the LORD</span><span class="H559 s"> saith</span><span class="H3282 s">, Because</span><span class="H1323 s"> the daughters</span><span class="H6726 s"> of Zion</span><span class="H1361 s"> are haughty</span><span class="H3212 s">, and walk</span><span class="H5186 s"> with stretched forth</span><span class="H1627 s"> necks</span><span class="H8265 s"> and wanton</span><span class="H5869 s"> eyes</span><span class="H1980 s">, walking</span><span class="H2952 s"> and mincing</span><span class="H3212 s"> <i>as</i> they go</span><span class="H5913 s">, and making a tinkling</span><span class="H7272 s"> with their feet</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (wanton…: Heb. deceiving with their eyes) (mincing: or, tripping nicely)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.3.17"><span class="H136 s">Therefore the Lord</span><span class="H5596 s"> will smite with a scab</span><span class="H6936 s"> the crown of the head</span><span class="H1323 s"> of the daughters</span><span class="H6726 s"> of Zion</span><span class="H3068 s">, and the LORD</span><span class="H6168 s"> will discover</span><span class="H6596 s"> their secret parts</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (discover: Heb. make naked)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.3.18"><span class="H3117 s">In that day</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H5493 s"> will take away</span><span class="H8597 s"> the bravery</span><span class="H5914 s"> of <i>their</i> tinkling ornaments</span><span class="H7636 s"> <i>about their feet</i>, and <i>their</i> cauls</span><span class="H7720 s">, and <i>their</i> round tires like the moon</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (cauls: or, networks)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.3.19"><span class="H5188 s">The chains</span><span class="H8285 s">, and the bracelets</span><span class="H7479 s">, and the mufflers</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (chains: or, sweet balls) (mufflers: or, spangled ornaments)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.3.20"><span class="H6287 s">The bonnets</span><span class="H6807 s">, and the ornaments of the legs</span><span class="H7196 s">, and the headbands</span><span class="H5315 s">, and the tablets</span><span class="H1004 s"> †</span><span class="H3908 s">, and the earrings</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (tablets: Heb. houses of the soul)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.3.21"><span class="H2885 s">The rings</span><span class="H639 s">, and nose</span><span class="H5141 s"> jewels</span>,</div> 
<div id="v290.3.22"><span class="H4254 s">The changeable suits of apparel</span><span class="H4595 s">, and the mantles</span><span class="H4304 s">, and the wimples</span><span class="H2754 s">, and the crisping pins</span>,</div> 
<div id="v290.3.23"><span class="H1549 s">The glasses</span><span class="H5466 s">, and the fine linen</span><span class="H6797 s">, and the hoods</span><span class="H7289 s">, and the vails</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.3.24"><span class="H1314 s">And it shall come to pass, <i>that</i> instead of sweet smell</span><span class="H4716 s"> there shall be stink</span><span class="H2290 s">; and instead of a girdle</span><span class="H5364 s"> a rent</span><span class="H4639 s">; and instead of well set</span><span class="H4748 s"> hair</span><span class="H7144 s"> baldness</span><span class="H6614 s">; and instead of a stomacher</span><span class="H4228 s"> a girding</span><span class="H8242 s"> of sackcloth</span><span class="H3587 s">; <i>and</i> burning</span><span class="H3308 s"> instead of beauty</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.3.25"><span class="H4962 s">Thy men</span><span class="H5307 s"> shall fall</span><span class="H2719 s"> by the sword</span><span class="H1369 s">, and thy mighty</span><span class="H4421 s"> in the war</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (mighty: Heb. might)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.3.26"><span class="H6607 s">And her gates</span><span class="H578 s"> shall lament</span><span class="H56 s"> and mourn</span><span class="H5352 s">; and she <i>being</i> desolate</span><span class="H3427 s"> shall sit</span><span class="H776 s"> upon the ground</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (desolate: or, emptied: Heb. cleansed)</span></div></div>

